# Phase 7 — Complete Hockey Gameplay Simulation

Current phase: Phase 7.

This phase builds the full hockey gameplay simulation without final networking.

## Required library

Create `hockey_gameplay`.

Dependency:

```text
hockey_gameplay -> hockey_core, hockey_ecs, hockey_physics
```

## Required gameplay model

Implement 4v4 hockey with 2 teams, 3 skaters + 1 goalie per team, 1 puck, 2 goals, periods/timer, score, faceoffs, goals, spawn/reset flow.

## Required components

Implement `PlayerComponent`, `SkaterComponent`, `GoalieComponent`, `PuckGameplayComponent`, `StickComponent`, `TeamStateComponent`, `MatchStateComponent`, `ScoreComponent`, `PossessionComponent`, `ShotComponent`, `PassComponent`, `CheckComponent`, `FaceoffComponent`, and `RespawnComponent`.

## Required systems

Implement match setup, team/role assignment, skater movement, goalie movement, puck control, stick handling, shooting, passing, checking/contact, goal detection, score, match clock, periods, faceoffs, respawn/reset, out-of-play handling if used, and gameplay camera data if needed.

## Input model

Define gameplay input data independent from SDL. Gameplay must not directly read SDL input.

## Server-readiness

Gameplay must use fixed timestep, have no renderer/editor dependency, no direct SDL/Vulkan/ImGui dependency, and no direct networking dependency unless explicitly allowed.

## Required tests

Create `HockeyGameplayTests` covering match setup, scene validation, spawn/team/role assignment, puck reset, goal detection, score, faceoff, match timer, skater/goalie movement, shooting/pass/check paths, and server-mode fixed tick.

## Definition of done

Phase 7 is complete only when 4v4 match initializes, gameplay tests pass, puck/goals/score/timer/movement/stick interactions/shooting/passing/checking/faceoffs work, server can run gameplay headlessly, client can run local gameplay, and gameplay does not depend on renderer.
